The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Railways beat Delhi
                                                   Railways beat Delhi
                      
	Chennai: Railways defeated Delhi 1-0 on the opening day of the 63rd National Football Championship for Santosh Trophy in Tiruvallore on Sunday.         
	Railways survived some anxious moments before Abhishek scored the all-important goal in the 44th minute.         
	Meanwhile, riding a brilliant hattrick by striker Riju (14th, 76th, 84th), Tamil Nadu drubbed Rajasthan 7-0, with Suresh Kumar (47th and 53rd), Pradeep (27th) and D Ravanan (82nd) being the other scorers.         
	Mizoram spanked Pondicherry 4-0, while Tripura beat Himachal Pradesh 2-0.         
	 (PTI)                                                                                                                       
